Time Complexity:

Let n = number of people

    Each element is pushed and popped at most once → O(n)

Overall: O(n)


Space Complexity:

    Stack stores heights → O(n)

Overall: O(n)


Approach:

1. Create a stack to store heights of people on the right

2. Start from rightmost person:
   - Last person sees 0 people

3. Traverse from right to left:

   - Initialize count = 0

   - While stack is not empty and current height > stack top:
     → Pop smaller heights (they are fully visible)
     → Increment count

4. After popping:
   - If stack is empty → no taller person ahead → visible = count
   - Else → one taller person is also visible → visible = count + 1

5. Store result in same array

6. Push current height into stack

7. Continue for all elements

8. Return result array








class Solution {
    public int[] canSeePersonsCount(int[] h) {
        Stack<Integer> st = new Stack<>();
        int n=h.length;
        st.push(h[n-1]);
        h[n-1]=0;
        for(int i=n-2; i>=0; i--){
            int count = 0;
            int curr = h[i];
            while(st.size()>0 && h[i]>st.peek()){
                st.pop();
                count++;
            }

            if(st.size()==0) h[i] = count;
            else h[i] = count+1;

            st.push(curr);
        }
        return h;
    }
}
